solution.text:
There are eight major environmental factors that affects the rate of respiration and they are as follows:
  • Oxygen Content of the Atmosphere
  • Temperature
  • Light
  • Water Contents
  • Respirable Material
  • Carbon Dioxide concentration
  • Protoplasmic conditions
  • Other factors.

The rate of respiration depends upon the quality and quantity of protoplasm.
